<![CDATA[<div style=""><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" style="">Dear {!Fellow_Application__c.Applicant_First_Name__c},<br><br></font></div><div style=""><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Congratulations! We will be moving you forward to our matching pool and you will be among the candidates considered for a host placement.&nbsp;<br></font></div><div style=""><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></div><div style=""><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Next Steps</font></div><div style=""><ul><li><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">On the afternoon of&nbsp;<b>March 3rd</b>&nbsp;the 2023 project list page will be launched in the Climate Corps fellow portal.&nbsp;On this page, you will be able to view the list of 2022 host organizations and projects and choose your preferred host placements.&nbsp;<span class="NormalTextRun SCXW78364314 BCX0">You will receive a reminder email when the project list is available which will provide instructions and tips on selecting projects.</span></font></li><li><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Candidates who submit their preferences by&nbsp;<b>11:59pm PT on March 5th</b>&nbsp;will be considered placement.</font></li><li><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">We will evaluate finalists and notify those chosen to participate in our program of their host placement on&nbsp;<b>March 10th</b>. When determining your placement, we will consider your geographical and host preferences, skills, and project interests. Please note that entering into the matching pool does not guarantee a placement.&nbsp;</font></li><li><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">If you are matched with a host organization, you will have until <b>March 24th</b>&nbsp;to accept the placement.</font></li><li><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Finally, if you are an international student, please review our&nbsp;<a href="http://edfclimatecorps.org/sites/edfclimatecorps.org/files/edfcc_work_authorization_policy.pdf">Work Authorization Policy</a>.&nbsp; It details important procedures, and guidelines that will help ensure you are eligible for a summer fellowship.</font></li></ul></div><div style=""><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Due to the high volume of applications, we will be delayed in responding to emails and requests. However, should you have impending travel plans that will limit your communication or any other urgent notifications, please contact climatecorpsadmin@ceaconsulting.com. If at any time you would like to remove yourself from consideration, please let us know.<br><br></font></div><div style=""><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Best regards,&nbsp;</font></div><div style=""><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">The Climate Corps Team<br><br></font></div><div style=""><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" style=""><b style="">*Please do not reply to this email. We will not respond to any inquiries sent to this address. Please follow the instructions above to contact us.</b></font></div>]]></td>
</tr>
